-- India Corruption Matches Africa as Every Second Person Pays Bribe, ET Says
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2010-12-10T01:55:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-10/india-corruption-matches-africa-as-every-second-person-pays-bribe-et-says.html
More than half of Indians paid a
bribe in the past year, ranking the South Asian nation as the
ninth-most corrupt country in the world and on par with Sub-
Saharan Africa, the Economic Times reported, citing a survey by
Berlin-based Transparency International.  To contact the reporter on this story:
